## Layout Components

## SiteShell
Responsibility:
- wraps full page background, typography defaults, and max-width rhythm
- places skip link and main landmark

Props:
- children: React.ReactNode

## SectionContainer
Responsibility:
- consistent horizontal and vertical spacing across breakpoints
- optional narrow mode for text-heavy sections

Props:
- id?: string
- ariaLabel?: string
- narrow?: boolean
- className?: string
- children: React.ReactNode

## StickyHeader
Responsibility:
- desktop and mobile nav shell
- active section state and top blur behavior

Props:
- links: LinkTarget[]
- socialLinks: LinkTarget[]
- activeSectionId?: string

## SkipToContent
Responsibility:
- keyboard-only fast jump to main content

Props:
- targetId: string

## SiteFooter
Responsibility:
- minimal build-stack statement and copyright/meta

Props:
- text: string

---

## Navigation Components

## NavLinks
Responsibility:
- render anchor list for desktop and optional mobile variant

Props:
- links: LinkTarget[]
- activeSectionId?: string
- orientation?: "row" | "column"

## MobileNavSheet
Responsibility:
- compact menu for mobile with section anchors and social links

Props:
- links: LinkTarget[]
- socialLinks: LinkTarget[]
- open: boolean
- onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void

## ActiveSectionIndicator
Responsibility:
- lime accent underline or dot for current section

Props:
- active: boolean
- mode?: "underline" | "dot"

---

## Section Components

## HeroSection
Responsibility:
- headline, support copy, CTA row, ambient visual module
- enforces copy length discipline

Props:
- id: string
- headline: string
- supportingText: string
- ctas: LinkTarget[]
- visualVariant?: "grid" | "diagram" | "wave"

Acceptance notes:
- mobile order is text then visual
- max 3 CTA actions

## ExpertiseSection
Responsibility:
- render three capability cards with concise bullets

Props:
- id: string
- title: string
- groups: {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    bullets: string[];
  }[]

Acceptance notes:
- card readability preserved at 320 width

## ProofBlockSection
Responsibility:
- reusable proof block for both placeholder projects
- supports alternating desktop media/text order

Props:
- id: string
- label: string
- name: string
- description: string
- features: FeatureItem[]
- stack: StackTag[]
- media: {
    src: string;
    alt: string;
    aspectRatio: "16:10" | "16:9";
  }
- ctas: LinkTarget[]
- desktopMediaSide: "left" | "right"

Acceptance notes:
- mobile is always text first, media second
- cinematic section feel, not card grid

## PhilosophySection
Responsibility:
- headline, support paragraph, principle list

Props:
- id: string
- title: string
- supportingText: string
- principles: string[]

Acceptance notes:
- designed to scan in one desktop viewport

## ContactSection
Responsibility:
- conversion-focused prompt and primary external links

Props:
- id: string
- prompt: string
- links: LinkTarget[]

Acceptance notes:
- action links obvious and reachable in one tap from nav

